FBIS4-50862 "drchi099_v_94006" FBIS-CHI-94-099 Daily Report 22 May 1994 TAIWAN Official Urges Mainland Response to SEF Proposal Official Urges Mainland Response to SEF Proposal OW2305103994 Taipei China Broadcasting Corporation News Network in Mandarin 2300 GMT 22 May 94 OW2305103994 Taipei China Broadcasting Corporation News Network Mandarin BFN [From the "Hookup" program] [Text] Huang Kun-huei, chairman of the Mainland Affairs Council [MAC], Executive Yuan, pointed out yesterday [22 May] that in order to conclude the tasks related to dealing with the aftermath of the Qiandao Lake incident, Mainland China should respond quickly to the Strait Exchange Foundation [SEF] proposal made in early April for a special meeting between the SEF and the Association for Relations Across the Taiwan Straits [ARATS]. Chairman Huang Kun-huei added that whether the two nongovernmental organizations on both sides of the strait hold a special meeting on safety in the near future is not directly related to the convening of the second round of the Ku-Wang meeting. However, if the special meeting cannot be held for a long time, it will have an impact on arrangements for activities related to the Ku-Wang meeting. Chairman Huang Kun-huei made these remarks when answering reporters' questions on whether MAC and SEF have started coordinating and having contact to push forward the second round of the Ku-Wang meeting. As for SEF chairman Ku Chen-fu and Vice Chairman Chiao Jen-he advocating to push forward the second Ku-Wang meeting based on the agreement on institutionalized contacts and talks between the two organizations, Chairman Huang Kun-huei said MAC and SEF have not yet discussed the issue.
